= Installation and Quick Start =

== Requirements ==
* Minecraft 1.21.11
* Java 21+
* Fabric Loader
* Fabric API

== Install ==
# Download the StarScript jar.
# Place it in your Minecraft ''mods'' folder.
# Ensure Fabric API is installed.
# Launch the game.

== First Story in 4 Steps ==
# Create a story JSON file in a data pack at:
#* ''data/<namespace>/stories/<story_name>.json''
# Add a minimal story structure.
# Run ''/reload''.
# Start it with ''/story start <story_id>''.

== Minimal Story Example ==
<syntaxhighlight lang="json">
{
  "id": "my_story",
  "name": "My First Story",
  "description": "An interactive adventure",
  "start_node": "intro",
  "nodes": {
    "intro": {
      "id": "intro",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "text": ["Welcome to your adventure!"],
      "choices": [
        { "text": "Begin", "next": "chapter_1" }
      ]
    },
    "chapter_1": {
      "id": "chapter_1",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "text": ["Your story is now running."]
    }
  }
}
</syntaxhighlight>

== Verify ==
* ''/story list'' should show your story.
* ''/story info <story_id>'' should show node count and metadata.

